  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2018-11-15T05:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Retail Justice Review Act of 2018\n\nThis bill directs the Department of Justice to study the effectiveness of retail theft rehabilitation programs. A retail theft rehabilitation program is an education program that a retailer offers to a shoplifter instead of reporting a theft to law enforcement.\n\nAdditionally, the bill states that a retailer may offer a retail theft rehabilitation program in accordance with state, local, and tribal law."
